<subSubSection id="8C7E9E004E772CFB000D5923E77A7C14" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="72B9109F6844C762E8E8FA1970DBC52F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="5C9286010BC09F602327BA7F6ED4E66B" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristocera japonica subsp. ishigakiensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="japonica" subSpecies="ishigakiensis">Pristocera japonica ishigakiensis</taxonomicName>
Yasumatsu, 1955: 245. Holotype (male, KUF), type loc.: Kainan, Ishigaki-jima, Ryukyu Is., Japan. 
<taxonomicName id="8DFE871B7723F0731C0B34F9493217BC" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Acrepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acrepyris japonica subsp. ishigakiensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="japonica" subSpecies="ishigakiensis">Acrepyris japonica ishigakiensis</taxonomicName>
: Terayama, 1996: 595 (genus transfer). 
<taxonomicName id="76A89265EEC41D70E2D2E805E569F1F5" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Acrepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acrepyris ishigakiensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishigakiensis">Acrepyris ishigakiensis</taxonomicName>
: Terayama, 1999: 103 (raised to species). 
<taxonomicName id="9C4118831A6CC0D9EC010B3E92D9EFBD" baseAuthorityName="Yasumatsu" baseAuthorityYear="1955" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pristepyris ishigakiensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishigakiensis">Pristepyris ishigakiensis</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="7B681685688EA53C5EE1141473B82971" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4489.1.1" author="Azevedo, CO" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 294" refId="B8" refString="Azevedo, CO, Alencar, IDCC, Ramos, MS, Barbosa, DN, Colombo, WD, Vargas, RJM, Lim, J, 2018. Global guide of the flat wasps (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae). Zootaxa 4889 (1): 1 - 294, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4489.1.1" title="Global guide of the flat wasps (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4489.1.1" volume="4889" year="2018">Azevedo et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
: 104 (genus transfer).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4CD0F2EB23ED5A08259AE43FFE8BAB75" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="male diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CA6825C0E662E82CF46452F5A455F3DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA515EF88FCC44413322A2279D532446" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
TL ≈ 6.3-8.0 mm. HL/HW 
<normalizedToken id="CCD558A39D1D761D1CD73F986F937B63" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
100 = 95-100. Frons and vertex with deep foveolae (ca. 0.05-0.06 mm in diameter), of which intervals are smooth and shining and narrower than diameter of foveolae. Anterior clypeal margin nearly straight medially. Mandible with five apical teeth. Transverse pronotal carina present. Cervical pronotal area in lateral view forming an angulate corner. LP/WP = 1.10-1.16. Metapostnotal median carina incomplete posteriorly. Tergum II with longitudinal sulcus and ridge, sternum II with very weak longitudinal median carina or absent. Apical margin of hypopygium straight medially. Apical lobe of aedeagus in lateral view elongate and lobate, directed posteriad, weakly curved ventrad at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4A89C5955AA4D7049E30F3B843E8E700" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="female diagnosis">
<paragraph id="14338772E4AA07733EE86FF1938D3CDC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F46EE5EB714ABD7ADACF9CBE05197B94" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2943D55D29DE5163A58B28D3832AB2D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="3653519FD708E28DAAF4FE041C7058A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5255DE00EDAA1E38F7E3C6662D2AD039" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Full description was given by 
<bibRefCitation id="038A435DD157155801903008F42B1810" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5109/22656" author="Yasumatsu, K" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Faculty of Agriculture, Kyushu University" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="233 - 249" refId="B37" refString="Yasumatsu, K, 1955. Taxonomic notes on three wireworm parasites of the genus Pristocera from the Far East (Hymenoptera: Bethyloidea). Journal of the Faculty of Agriculture, Kyushu University 10 (3): 233 - 249, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5109/22656" title="Taxonomic notes on three wireworm parasites of the genus Pristocera from the Far East (Hymenoptera: Bethyloidea)." url="https://doi.org/10.5109/22656" volume="10" year="1955">Yasumatsu (1955)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="4EAF835EDD35DEC02C9F2352EB0DAECE" author="Terayama, M" editor="Yamane, S" journalOrPublisher="Hokkaido University Press: Sapporo, Japan" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="701 - 725" refId="B33" refString="Terayama, M, 1999. Description of new species of the family Bethylidae from the Ryukyus, and taxonomic notes on the Japanese species of the Sclerodermus. In: Yamane, S, Ikudome, S, Terayama, M, Eds., Identification Guide to the Aculeata of the Nansei Islands. Hokkaido University Press: Sapporo, Japan: 701 - 725" title="Description of new species of the family Bethylidae from the Ryukyus, and taxonomic notes on the Japanese species of the Sclerodermus." volumeTitle="Identification Guide to the Aculeata of the Nansei Islands." year="1999">Terayama (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. Additional information as below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="111C23FA1BA669179E37D06DC49088A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="BC126AB8943D0E68B2B5F02FA737C0E5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="AC73DB5EBEC731488EDED56A15A58E38" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
HL/ 
<normalizedToken id="70CB2E89941B60FD4DD876BBE18BB12F" originalValue="HW×">HWx</normalizedToken>
100 = 95-100 (98 in holotype). Frons and vertex with deep foveolae (ca. 0.05-0.06 mm in diameter), of which intervals are smooth and usually narrower than diameter of foveolae. Occipital carina present. Clypeus roundly produced anteriad; median clypeal carina moderately distinct, almost reaching anterior clypeal margin; anterior clypeal margin weakly incurved medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C750520DF97B69D041A5F3B5F94AE15F" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Pristepyris seqalu sp. nov., male, holotype (TP 170606 _ 26) A head in full-face view B antenna (left) C mandible D mesosoma in lateral view E mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carina absent F fore-wing G hindwing. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686032" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4C</figureCitation>
). Compound eye large and convex, with sparse thin erect setae. Mandible with five teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D91D5CE1D78D8EF7D5E350F36F67019F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="72740DA6BCBC37068494EF2F4B766B6F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="A2A35839819E2027F1799CADBD74309C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Dorsal area of pronotum smooth and shining, with deep foveolae; distinct transverse pronotal carinae present (arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FD89369ECBAE5061FD3AC02A2DB51B4A" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pristepyris ishigakiensis, male, A-E, G, H, JI 170808 _ 34, F, TH 190717 _ 42 A head in full-face view B antenna (right) C mandible D mesosoma in lateral view; arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area E mesosoma in dorsal view; arrows indicating posterior transverse margin extending to spiracle F mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carina present G forewing H hindwing. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686034" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6F</figureCitation>
); cervical pronotal area in lateral view forming an angulate corner (arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CF7037E75B78A2634158A7AA2B1FDF73" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pristepyris ishigakiensis, male, A-E, G, H, JI 170808 _ 34, F, TH 190717 _ 42 A head in full-face view B antenna (right) C mandible D mesosoma in lateral view; arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area E mesosoma in dorsal view; arrows indicating posterior transverse margin extending to spiracle F mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carina present G forewing H hindwing. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686034" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6D</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron elongate; anterior, upper and lower fovea distinct; acropleural area smooth and shining, with sparse and small foveolae. Mesopleural pit absent. Mesodiscrimen concave, with weak median carina. Metasternum with metafurcal pit. Lateral face of metapectal-propodeal complex irregularly rugose entirely. Metapectal-propodeal complex in dorsal view with LP/WP = 1.10-1.16, with lateral margins subparallel and slightly convex; metapostnotal median carina distinct, but incomplete posteriorly; submedian rugae irregularly running and incomplete posteriorly; sublateral margin incomplete posteriorly; posterior transverse margin indistinct or distinctly extending to spiracle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3EE8D374D25BE307BB9E98703C05B8BC" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pristepyris ishigakiensis, male, A-E, G, H, JI 170808 _ 34, F, TH 190717 _ 42 A head in full-face view B antenna (right) C mandible D mesosoma in lateral view; arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area E mesosoma in dorsal view; arrows indicating posterior transverse margin extending to spiracle F mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carina present G forewing H hindwing. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686034" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6E</figureCitation>
); dorsomedian and dorsolateral faces weakly rugoso-scabrous; median portion of propodeal declivity transversely rugoso-scabrous. Forewing with r-m2 flexion line (arrows in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="61D1D62858B0997087CA5EDB7D05ECD0" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Pristepyris ishigakiensis, male, A-E, G, H, JI 170808 _ 34, F, TH 190717 _ 42 A head in full-face view B antenna (right) C mandible D mesosoma in lateral view; arrow indicating an angulate corner present on cervical pronotal area E mesosoma in dorsal view; arrows indicating posterior transverse margin extending to spiracle F mesosoma in dorsal view; arrow indicating transverse pronotal carina present G forewing H hindwing. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686034" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6G</figureCitation>
), without R2 and 2M12 flexion line. Hindwing with five distal hamuli. Tarsal claws bifid, with thin and curved apical teeth.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9406916AD75A4B2A030969542D10F90A" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.84953.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686034" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
